\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces  As the number of steering prompts in our training dataset increases, the teraFLOPs (TFLOPS) required to attain a similar loss on a \textit  {held-in} evaluation set (steering prompts seen during training, but base prompt unseen during training) decreases for our best \textsc  {HyperSteer}\ variant (cross attention). This value is approximately constant for our dictionary learning baseline of \texttt  {ReFT-r1}. See Appendix\nobreakspace  {}\ref {appendix:flops} for details. \relax }}{3}{figure.caption.11}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:flop-limits}{{3}{3}{As the number of steering prompts in our training dataset increases, the teraFLOPs (TFLOPS) required to attain a similar loss on a \textit {held-in} evaluation set (steering prompts seen during training, but base prompt unseen during training) decreases for our best \methodname \ variant (cross attention). This value is approximately constant for our dictionary learning baseline of \texttt {ReFT-r1}. See Appendix~\ref {appendix:flops} for details. \relax }{figure.caption.11}{}}
